# Testing rules

## Layout

| Kind | Location | Pattern |
|------|----------|---------|
| unit | colocated in `libs/**` / `apps/**` | `*.spec.ts` |
| integration | `apps/<app>/test/integration` | `*.integration.spec.ts` |
| e2e | `apps/<app>/test/e2e` | `*.e2e-spec.ts` (config `test/jest-e2e.json`) |

Shared scaffold in `/test`: `setup/jest.setup.ts` (`reflect-metadata` + env
defaults), `setup/test-db.setup.ts` (DataSource + **run migrations**, never
synchronize), `helpers/` (`auth-test`, `database-test`, `request-test`),
`fixtures/` (`users`, `roles`, `permissions`).

## Rules

- Unit tests mock collaborators (no DB/Redis). e2e tests boot the Fastify app via
  `createTestApp(...)` and need real MySQL + Redis (CI services or
  `docker/docker-compose.test.yml`).
- Never enable `synchronize` in tests — run migrations.
- Assert the **unified envelope** in e2e: check `body.success` and `body.code`,
  not raw shapes.
- Reset state between e2e tests with `truncateAll()` + reseed, or `withRollback`.

## Must cover (platform behaviors)

login (success + wrong password + disabled), register (+ duplicate), refresh
(success + expired/invalid), permission (admin route with/without
`@Permissions`), rate-limit (over-limit + `X-RateLimit-*` headers), sso-callback
(bad `state` + happy path), audit (write enqueues `WRITE_OPERATION_LOG`, worker
persists), queue (correct `QUEUE_NAMES`/`JOB_NAMES`; unknown job throws),
migration (empty DB → current schema), seed (admin with `rbac:*` + base
dictionaries).
